Module 101
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 101 – Testimony Architecture: From First‑Person to Public Record 🗣️📜
⚖️ Core Message
Write testimony that stands alone as evidence: specific dates, quotes, and exhibits; neutral tone; a single, narrow ask.

📖 Lesson Content
• Structure — Timeline paragraphs with pin‑cites; exhibits labeled.
• Voice — Facts, not feelings; quotes in quotation marks with source.
• Ask — One procedural remedy the body can grant immediately.
• Attachments — Top‑5 exhibits (hashed) + index.
• Reuse — Link your archive so others can verify.
📝 Assignment
Draft a 2‑page testimony with five pin‑cited facts and a single procedural ask, attaching an exhibit index with hashes.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
TESTIMONY (EXCERPT)
On 06/12, I served the complaint (Ex. A, LC0001). On 07/10, the portal issued Receipt #8472 (Ex. C). We ask for a deficiency order per Rule 5(d)(4).

💡 Reflection
Testimony persuades when it’s easy to check and easy to grant.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A short speech bubble next to a page of exhibits with a hash manifest.



