Module 102
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 102 – Narrative Without Noise: Editing for Judges and Journalists ✂️📰
⚖️ Core Message
Trim prose until only proof and relevance remain. Use parallel summaries: 150‑word abstract + one‑pager + two‑pager with citations.

📖 Lesson Content
• Abstract — 150 words, three facts with pin‑cites, one ask.
• One‑Pager — Headings: Problem • Evidence • Standard • Ask.
• Two‑Pager — Add background and sources; no adjectives.
• Fact Check — Peer verify cites; remove unsupported lines.
• Formatting — Use lists, short paragraphs, and white space.
📝 Assignment
Produce all three versions (150‑word, one‑pager, two‑pager) on the same issue with pin‑cites and hashes.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
150‑WORD ABSTRACT (EXCERPT)
Three timely tenders; no deficiency order; we ask for nunc pro tunc acceptance.

💡 Reflection
The shorter it gets, the more the remaining words must be right.

🎨 Visual Pairing
Three stacked sheets labeled 150w • 1p • 2p with the same citation spine.



