Module 103
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 103 – The People’s Law School: Turn Modules Into a Short Course 🎓📘
⚖️ Core Message
Package selected modules into a 4‑session course with assignments, model answers, and a public syllabus.

📖 Lesson Content
• Syllabus — Four sessions: Filing, Evidence, Paper Hearing, Appeals.
• Materials — Handouts (Modules 1,4,44,30) + assignments + keys.
• Delivery — 90 minutes per session; recording and slides.
• Assessment — Pass/fail based on three filed deliverables.
• License — Open license for reuse; encourage forks.
📝 Assignment
Publish a 4‑session syllabus with links to handouts, assignments, and answer keys; add a course README.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
COURSE OUTLINE
S1 Filing is Protest; S2 Evidence Lives in the Record; S3 Paper Hearing; S4 Frame the Appeal.

💡 Reflection
Education scales reform—especially when free and forkable.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A chalkboard with four session titles and a link icon.



