Module 105
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 105 – Pattern Brief: One Brief, Many Courts 📍📑
⚖️ Core Message
Write a pattern brief with core law and modular facts so allies can adapt it to their case with minimal edits.

📖 Lesson Content
• Core — Doctrine sections (Younger, Ex parte Young, Winter) with neutral citations.
• Slots — Bracketed places for facts, ECF cites, exhibit IDs.
• Appendices — Templates for orders, declarations, and indices.
• QA — 'Replace all' check; local‑rules appendix.
• Distribution — Publish as versioned template with change log.
📝 Assignment
Produce a 6‑page pattern brief skeleton with bracketed slots and an appendix list.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
SKELETON (EXCERPT)
[FACT TIMELINE] → [LEGAL STANDARD] → [APPLICATION] → [RELIEF].

💡 Reflection
Templates save time and prevent error—when they’re well‑marked and verified.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A brief outline with highlighted bracketed fields.



