Module 106
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 106 – Community Standards: Style, Citations, Corrections 📐🧭
⚖️ Core Message
Adopt shared standards so contributions mesh: one citation style, one corrections policy, one tone guide.

📖 Lesson Content
• Style — Headings, lists, fonts, and emoji usage (or not).
• Citations — Ex/Bates/Hash first; docket second; links last.
• Corrections — Visible log; version tags; errata notices.
• Tone — Neutral verbs; no speculation; proof over adjectives.
• Review — Quarterly review and update of standards.
📝 Assignment
Publish a 'Community Standards' page and apply it to two recent posts or briefs.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
ERRATA ENTRY
2025‑09‑03: Fixed hash typo for Ex. C.

💡 Reflection
Standards enable many hands to produce one coherent archive.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A style guide page with checkmarks on 'Cites' and 'Corrections'.



