Module 107
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 107 – Coalition Ledger: Who Verified What, When 📓✅
⚖️ Core Message
Track who verified which exhibit and when, so outside trust can build quickly.

📖 Lesson Content
• Ledger — Columns: Exhibit, Hash, Verifier, Date, Notes.
• Permissions — Consent to list names/initials; privacy tiers.
• Use — Cite the ledger in briefs and press kits.
• Updates — Rolling entries; hash re‑checks for major releases.
• Transparency — Publish redacted ledger publicly.
📝 Assignment
Create a coalition ledger and log at least three verifications with witness declarations.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
LEDGER ROW
Ex. A, 3f2c…, J.D. (09/02/25), 'Matches'.

💡 Reflection
A trustworthy ledger is a coalition’s resume.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A notebook icon with three initials and dates checked off.



