Module 108
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 108 – Platform Resilience: Surviving Takedowns & Drift 🛡️🌐
⚖️ Core Message
Assume platforms will change. Keep content portable, mirrored, and rebuildable from your manifests.

📖 Lesson Content
• Exports — Regular Notion/Drive/GitHub exports; test restores.
• Permalinks — Short slugs; redirect strategy; QR updates.
• Offline — Local, encrypted backups; printed Top‑10 where appropriate.
• Takedowns — Appeal processes; scripts for re‑upload.
• Continuity — Successor maintainers; documented credentials.
📝 Assignment
Write a 'Platform Resilience' SOP and run a restore test of one component (e.g., Top‑10).

✅ Model Answer (Template)
RESILIENCE CHECK
Restored Top‑10.pdf from backup v1.2. Hash matches manifest.

💡 Reflection
Portability is freedom; manifests are your compass.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A shield icon over three platform logos and a backup arrow.



