Module 109
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 109 – Trust Signals: How Strangers Decide to Help 🧭🤲
⚖️ Core Message
Strangers look for fast signals: clear citations, polite tone, quick verification, and modest asks. Design your materials for them.

📖 Lesson Content
• First Impression — Short landing page with 'How to Verify' and Top‑3 asks.
• Speed — Pin‑cites and hashes near the first claim.
• Asks — Time‑boxed; specific; single step (verify three exhibits).
• Feedback — Provide a response email and form; reply within 48 hours.
• Continuity — Public changelog shows activity and care.
📝 Assignment
Create a 'Start Here' page that includes a 60‑second verification demo and a 'Verify Three Exhibits' ask.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
ASK (BUTTON)
'Verify Exhibits A–C (2 minutes)' → link to Top‑10.pdf + ledger entry form.

💡 Reflection
Trust grows when you make it easy for someone new to do one good thing.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A 'Start Here' card with a verify button and a short video thumbnail.



