📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 111 – Institutional Pitch: Libraries, Labs, Clinics 🏛️📨
⚖️ Core Message
Pitch institutions with a clear value prop: what they get, how it’s verified, and what you’re asking them to host or teach.

📖 Lesson Content
• Targets — Law libraries, university labs, legal aid clinics.
• Value — Open, verified, reusable procedural education.
• Packet — One‑pager, Top‑10, Education Pack, governance note.
• Ask — Host archive; adopt course; join verification network.
• Follow‑up — Metrics and a quarterly call.
📝 Assignment
Draft a 1‑page institutional pitch email + a 2‑page attachment listing what you provide and what you ask.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
PITCH (EXCERPT)
We offer a verified procedural archive with a 4‑session course. We ask you to host and help verify updates quarterly.

💡 Reflection
Institutions move slowly; show that you’ve already done the hard work.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A letter icon with a library seal and a small 'Top‑10' thumbnail.



