Module 112
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 112 – Healthy Disagreement: Handling Critique Without Derailing 🧠🗣️
⚖️ Core Message
Invite critiques that improve the record. Use a visible corrections policy and answer in public with proof and updates.

📖 Lesson Content
• Policy — Corrections log; response windows; gratitude for fixes.
• Tone — Thank critics; fix what’s right; explain what’s not with cites.
• Channels — Issues/PRs; email; form; avoid flame wars.
• Examples — Show past fixes to build confidence.
• Boundaries — Moderation guidelines; safety first.
📝 Assignment
Publish a short 'How We Handle Critique' note and link it from your archive sidebar.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
REPLY (EXCERPT)
Thanks—corrected Ex. B hash (see corrections log 09/03). Other points addressed at ECF 25 at 3.

💡 Reflection
Critique handled well is free quality assurance.

🎨 Visual Pairing
Two speech bubbles with a small checkmark and a link to 'Corrections'.



