📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 113 – Teaching the Archive: Workshops and Office Hours 🧑‍🏫🗂️
⚖️ Core Message
Offer live workshops and office hours where others learn to verify and file. Keep it simple and hands‑on.

📖 Lesson Content
• Agenda — Verify one exhibit; draft one page; file one narrow ask.
• Resources — Slides + handouts + short video demos.
• Schedule — Monthly office hours; signup form; recorded sessions.
• Metrics — Count verified exhibits and filed pages post‑workshop.
• Sustain — Rotate hosts; publish a 'how to host' guide.
📝 Assignment
Create a workshop outline and an office‑hours schedule with links to materials.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
WORKSHOP: Verify Ex. A (hash match) → Draft Paper Hearing Q&A → Upload to Git mirror.

💡 Reflection
Teaching multiplies your impact with minimal overhead.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A calendar with 'Workshop' and 'Office Hours' stickers.



