Module 114
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 114 – Case Studies: Converting Lived Experience into Curriculum 📚🔍
⚖️ Core Message
Turn a single matter into teachable units with exhibits and assignments others can run without you.

📖 Lesson Content
• Structure — Summary; timeline; exhibits; assignments; answer keys.
• Fit — Map units to doctrines: service, findings, abstention, appeals.
• Permissions — Redactions and consents for public use.
• Assessment — Simple rubrics for pass/fail.
• Feedback — Collect improvements from instructors.
📝 Assignment
Publish one case study unit with a timeline, three exhibits, and an assignment with key.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
CASE UNIT: 'Deficiency Orders within 3 Days' — timeline + Ex. A–C + assignment.

💡 Reflection
Curriculum keeps memory alive and useful.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A binder labeled 'Case Unit' with tabs: Timeline • Exhibits • Assignment.



