Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 116 – Funding Without Capture: Sustain the Mission 💡💶
⚖️ Core Message
Resource the project without trading away independence: small grants, fellowships, or community support with clear guardrails.

📖 Lesson Content
• Sources — Microgrants, fellowships, philanthropic funds; no-strings basics.
• Guardrails — Public budgets; no editorial control; conflict disclosures.
• Tiers — Fund verification, education, or tooling separately.
• Accounting — Simple statements; open ledgers for public work.
• Ethics — Decline money that undermines core values.
📝 Assignment
Draft a 1‑page funding memo listing targets, guardrails, and a 6‑month budget for verification + education.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
BUDGET (EXCERPT)
Verification: $X; Education: $Y; Tooling: $Z; Admin: $A.

💡 Reflection
Transparency keeps funding aligned with justice, not influence.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A small budget table with a 'guardrails' sidebar.



