Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 117 – Exit Interviews: Capture What Worked (and What Didn’t) 📝🔍
⚖️ Core Message
Interview allies and opponents to learn and log improvements. Use structured questions and publish anonymized takeaways.

📖 Lesson Content
• Question Set — What helped? What hindered? What should change?
• Consent — Written; option to anonymize.
• Synthesis — Themes with quotes and exhibit cross‑refs.
• Action — Turn lessons into commits: change docs, templates, SOPs.
• Respect — Keep raw transcripts restricted.
📝 Assignment
Conduct two exit interviews and publish a 1‑page anonymized summary with three action items.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
THEME (EXCERPT)
'Checklists reduced errors' (Clinician). Action: add checklists to Tier 3 index.

💡 Reflection
Learning in public improves the work and the trust.

🎨 Visual Pairing
Speech bubbles feeding into a checklist with three new items.



