Module 118
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 8 — Epilogue & Advanced Testimony
Module 118 – Legacy: Stewardship, Not Ownership 🧭📦
⚖️ Core Message
You started it; others will carry it. Leave space, invite forks, and bless adaptation so memory outgrows authorship.

📖 Lesson Content
• Stewardship — Facilitate and maintain; avoid bottlenecks.
• License — Open and clear; encourage derivatives with attribution.
• Culture — Praise contributors; welcome corrections; be specific.
• Succession — Identify future stewards and document roles.
• Story — Frame the work as a commons.
📝 Assignment
Write a 'Legacy Statement' describing how others should steward, fork, and credit this archive in the future.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
LEGACY (EXCERPT)
This is a public, procedural commons. Fork freely; verify rigorously; credit contributors; care for the record.

💡 Reflection
The most durable memory is shared memory.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A relay baton labeled 'Archive' being passed between hands.



